forms -->
!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
padding 1em 2em ---- 1em will be top and buttom and 2em will be left and right
!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

<div> is a block element just like span but for components so that we can
give them a class and then add a style to the items in them.
<form>
    action="smth" attribut - which url/file to send the information to
    method="get, post, put" -- what method to use 
    for attr -> has to have value equal to the id of the input and then
    if we click on the text of the label it will select the radion button for example.

    <label for="fname">The name of the field</label>
    <input type="text" id="fname" name="fname"> -- this is the field on which we type
    if we set value='John' this will be the default value of the input 
    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
    the above will create a button with submit text

    requered=true -- will make the input required and the browser will show it to the user
    value - the default value 
    name - the name of the input
    placeholder - a hint that describes the expected value of the input
    autofocus - focuses on this input when the page is loaded
    disabled - not active input
    min or max - specifies the min and max values

    input types:
    text, number, password, email, search
    checkbox, radio, range, submit, button, file 
    email, url, tel(telephone)
    reset - makes a reset button 

    for radio buttons --> all radio inputs must be with the same name.
    if they are with different names we would be able to select all of them and \
    the idea is to select only one. if the names are the same we can select only one.

    <fieldset>
        used to group related data in the form
        <fieldset>
            <legend> details</legend> --> legend is the title of the fieldset
        </fieldset>
        <fieldset>
            <legend>order details</legend>
        </fieldset>
    </fieldset>

    <label for="size">Size:</label> the title of the select field in the form 
    <select id="size" name="size"> makes a select field for the user to choose from some options
        <option value="41">41</option>
        <option value="42">42</option>
    </select>

    <textarea rows="10" cols="10">
        area for a long text.
        without rows and cols we can adjust the size via css
    </textarea>

    <button type="menu"></button>
    types - button, menu, reset, submit
</form>

TABLES -->
<table> - creates a table
<th> this is the table head or the title of the table
<tr> table row 
<td> this is the table cell in the row

<table>
<thead> title of the table
<tbody> the body of the table
<tr>
<th> the first row with the names of the values below
<tr>
<td>
... 
<tfoot> footer in the table




semantic tags html -->
these tag's names describe their role in the html document.
so that this role can be read by the browser or other software/developers

<header></header>
<nav></nav>
<main></main>
<aside></aside>
<footer></footer>
<section></section>
<article></article>
<figure>
    to add a picture
    <figcaption>to add a text to the picture</figcaption>
</figure>

<details> additional details which the user can view or hide
    <summary>A visible heading to the details.</summary>
    <p>more info</p>
</details>

<time>for time(10:00)</time>
<address>for address(6 street, Greenland)</address>

